In this article, President Trump discusses the relationship between the United States and China and announces several measures to protect American security and prosperity. He accuses China of engaging in misconduct, such as intellectual property theft and violating trade commitments. He also criticizes China's handling of the COVID-19 pandemic, accusing them of a cover-up and allowing the virus to spread globally. As a result, the United States will terminate its relationship with the World Health Organization and redirect funds to other global public health needs. President Trump also addresses China's actions in Hong Kong, condemning their imposition of control and violation of treaty obligations. He announces the process of eliminating policy exemptions that give Hong Kong special treatment and the revision of the State Department's travel advisory for the territory. The United States will also take steps to sanction Chinese and Hong Kong officials involved in eroding Hong Kong's autonomy.